    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1. By genetic depletion of CtBP1 using shRNA in combination with synaptopHluorins to measure synaptic vesicle cycling, the authors show a defect in the endocytosis of synaptic vesicles. This is confirmed also in CtBP1 KO mice (Figure S2G). This effects can be rescued by expressing again CtBP1 (Figure 4C, D).\n\n18/01/2021 Dnyanada: The endocytic half times, t1/2 from Syt1 uptake assays (Figure 4) indicates a significantly lower rate of endocytosis in CtBP1KD compared to the control which is rescued by EGFP-CtBP1 in CtBP1KD cells. Based on this, the ontology term \"synaptic vesicle endocytosis\" was used. Given that the effect on SV endocytosis is not huge in KO/KI experiments, the \"regulator\" box was ticked.. Experimental description: Cells and tissues used in this study were obtained from Wistar rats, Sprague-Dawley rats, C57BL/6N mice and Ctbp1tm1Sor (Ctbp1 KO) mouse strain (Hildebrand and Soriano, 2002) backcrossed to C57BL/6N. Animals of both sexes were used.",
